{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic on Charles de Gaulle", "text_new": "{{See also|2020 coronavirus pandemic on naval ships}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic on Charles de Gaulle}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:2020 coronavirus pandemic on ''Charles de Gaulle''}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic on board ''Charles de Gaulle''\n| image = French aircraft carrier Charles de Gaulle (R91) underway on 24 April 2019 (190424-M-BP588-1005).jpg\n| caption = ''Charles de Gaulle'' in April 2019\n| map1 = \n| legend1 = \n| map2 = \n| legend2 = \n| map3 = \n| legend3 = \n| disease = [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[North Sea]]\n| first_case = {{ship|French aircraft carrier|Charles de Gaulle||2}}\n| arrival_date = April 10, 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=04|day1=10|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = \n| recovery_cases = 0\n| deaths = 0\n| confirmed_cases = 50\n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili = \n| website = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached {{ship|French aircraft carrier|Charles de Gaulle||2}} in April 2020.\n\n==Timeline==\nBecause about 40 crew members were beginning to show symptoms recently, the French aircraft carrier {{ship|French aircraft carrier|Charles de Gaulle||2}} set sail to its home port in [[Toulon]] earlier than planned, as reported on 8 April 2020 by the [[Ministry of Armed Forces (France)|Ministry of Armed Forces]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.france24.com/fr/20200408-coronavirus-plusieurs-cas-suspects-\u00e0-bord-du-porte-avions-fran\u00e7ais-charles-de-gaulle |title=Coronavirus : plusieurs cas suspects \u00e0 bord du porte-avions fran\u00e7ais Charles-de-Gaulle |language=French |work=France 24 |trans-title=Coronavirus: several suspected cases on board the French aircraft carrier Charles de Gaulle |date=8 April 2020 |access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"reuters-heading\">{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-france-military/french-military-ship-heading-back-to-port-due-to-possible-covid-19-cases-idUSKBN21Q0SY |title=French aircraft carrier heads home early due to possible COVID-19 cases |work=Reuters |date=8 April 2020 |access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref> After 66 tests were conducted on board, the ministry announced on 10 April that 50 tests had returned positive.<ref name=\"gaulle.parisien\">{{cite web |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/politique/coronavirus-50-cas-de-contamination-a-bord-du-charles-de-gaulle-trois-marins-evacues-10-04-2020-8297511.php |title=Coronavirus : 50 cas de contamination \u00e0 bord du \"Charles-de-Gaulle\", trois marins \u00e9vacu\u00e9s |work=Le Parisien |language=French |date=10 April 2020 |access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> Three sailors were evacuated by air to {{ill|Saint Anne Army Teaching Hospital|fr|H\u00f4pital d'instruction des arm\u00e9es Sainte-Anne}}.<ref name=\"gaulle.parisien\" /><ref name=\"gaulle.times\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/04/10/world/europe/10reuters-health-coronavirus-france-aircraftcarrier.html|title=France Reports 50 COVID-19 Cases Aboard Aircraft Carrier |website=The New York Times |agency=Reuters |date=10 April 2020 |access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> There are 1,760 personnel on board.<ref name=\"reuters-heading\"/> \nThe carrier arrived in Toulon on the afternoon of 12 April where the personnel is quarantined for 14 days.\nFirst, the origin of the outbreak was unknown; there has been no contact with the outside world after the ship made a stopover in [[Brest, France|Brest]] the middle of March.<ref name=\"franceinfo\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/coronavirus-le-porte-avions-francais-charles-de-gaulle-et-ses-50-cas-de-covid-19-a-bord-est-attendu-a-toulon-dimanche-apres-midi_3910907.html|title=Coronavirus : le porte-avions fran\u00e7ais \"Charles-de-Gaulle\", et ses 50 cas de Covid-19 \u00e0 bord, est attendu \u00e0 Toulon dimanche apr\u00e8s-midi|language=fr|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref><ref>[https://www.europe1.fr/societe/covid-19-a-bord-du-charles-de-gaulle-les-marins-qui-nont-pas-respecte-les-regles-doivent-etre-sanctionnes-3961696 www.europe1.fr] writes 'entre le 13 et le 16 mars'</ref>\n\nThe captain had given the crew orders to avoid an infection; a family day was cancelled. \nThe girlfriend of a sailor said in an interview on Easter Sunday that some sailors had eaten in the same restaurants as their wives or families. She also said that sailors of other nationalities had been there, too.<ref>www.europe1.fr: [https://www.europe1.fr/societe/covid-19-a-bord-du-charles-de-gaulle-les-marins-qui-nont-pas-respecte-les-regles-doivent-etre-sanctionnes-3961696 ''Les marins du Charles-de-Gaulle \"qui n\u2019ont pas respect\u00e9 les r\u00e8gles doivent \u00eatre sanctionn\u00e9s\"]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n{{#related:2019-20 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in France}}\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic on USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71)}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in military history]]\n[[Category:Maritime incidents in 2020]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by location|Charles de Gaulle]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|Charles de Gaulle]]\n[[Category:Aircraft carriers involved in the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|Charles de Gaulle]]\n[[Category:History of the French Navy]]\n[[Category:Maritime incidents in Europe]]\n[[Category:Military history of the North Sea]]\n[[Category:Water transport in the North Sea]]\n[[Category:Health disasters in Europe]]\n[[Category:Disasters in the North Sea]]\n[[Category:Health and transport]]\n[[Category:Health and military]]\n[[Category:Non-combat naval accidents]]\n\n\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n{{France-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{See also|2020 coro